================================================================================
   UBUNTU 22.04 TO 24.04 LTS UPGRADE -  SOLUTION
================================================================================

+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Customer         |                                                            |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Problem          | Manually performing in-place OS upgrades from Ubuntu       |
| Statement        | 22.04 LTS to Ubuntu 24.04 LTS has been a time consuming   |
|                  | activity where no proper pre-upgrade health checks,        |
|                  | post-upgrade validation or repo management are done with   |
|                  | a consistent and repeatable approach.                      |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Goal Statement   | To ensure automated end-to-end in-place OS upgrades from  |
|                  | Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (Jammy) to Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Noble       |
|                  | Numbat) without any manual work, where pre-upgrade health  |
|                  | checks, upgrade execution, post-upgrade validation and     |
|                  | cleanup are handled by shell scripts.                      |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Benefits         | - Accurate and consistent upgrade execution.               |
| Proposed         | - 100% reduction of manual upgrade steps.                  |
|                  | - 90-180 minutes of manual effort reduced per server.      |
|                  | - Unattended overnight execution across multiple servers.  |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Key Actions      | - Script 1: Runs pre-upgrade health checks, patches OS     |
| Taken            |   to latest 22.04 packages, and launches do-release-       |
|                  |   upgrade in background (30-60 mins).                      |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Script 2: Runs post-upgrade cleanup, re-enables repos,   |
|                  |   refreshes apt package lists and reboots server (5 mins). |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Collect system state info (OS version, disk space,       |
|                  |   running services) before upgrade begins.                 |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Perform pre-upgrade checks: OS version must be 22.04,   |
|                  |   minimum 5-10 GB free disk space, no broken packages.    |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Backup APT sources before making any changes.            |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Disable third-party repos (Docker, Kubernetes, Foreman)  |
|                  |   to prevent conflicts during upgrade.                     |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Fully patch 22.04 packages before triggering upgrade.    |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Stop Qualys security agent to prevent interference       |
|                  |   during upgrade (auto-restarts after reboot).             |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Execute upgrade via do-release-upgrade in non-           |
|                  |   interactive background mode with full logging.           |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Post-upgrade: verify OS is Ubuntu 24.04, check for      |
|                  |   failed services, broken packages, and disk health.       |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Re-point server to internal Foreman/Pulp Noble (24.04)  |
|                  |   package mirrors and remove stale Jammy repo references.  |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Accept a list of servers and loop through them           |
|                  |   sequentially for batch upgrades.                         |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | - Run the upgrade unattended overnight.                    |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
| Use Cases        | 1. Upgrades Ubuntu 22 servers hosting websites/APIs.       |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 2. Upgrade the OS without migrating the data for           |
|                  |    MySQL/PostgreSQL databases.                              |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 3. Application servers like Java/.Net/Node.js are          |
|                  |    upgraded OS without migrating the application to        |
|                  |    new server.                                             |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 4. Ubuntu 22.04 LTS support ends April 2027, this         |
|                  |    proactive upgrade avoids security gaps and              |
|                  |    compliance issues.                                      |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 5. CI/CD Pipeline Servers (Jenkins/GitLab): Upgrade        |
|                  |    build agents without disrupting active pipelines.       |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 6. Monitoring Servers (Prometheus/Grafana/ELK): Upgrade    |
|                  |    without losing historical metrics or log data.          |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 7. VMware/Virtual Machine Environments: Take VM snapshot   |
|                  |    before upgrade as a rollback point, then run scripts.   |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 8. Kubernetes Worker Nodes: Drain node, upgrade OS,        |
|                  |    rejoin cluster, validate node status post-upgrade.      |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 9. Docker/Container Host Servers: Upgrade host OS without  |
|                  |    affecting running containers.                           |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 10. Batch/Scheduled Job Servers: Upgrade servers running   |
|                  |     cron/scheduled jobs and validate post-reboot.          |
|                  |                                                            |
|                  | 11. Audit & Logging: Full upgrade log captured for         |
|                  |     compliance reporting and audit trail.                  |
+------------------+------------------------------------------------------------+
